premise_source_doc_sentence: Duane Hopwood is a 2005 film featured in the Sundance Film Festival starring David Schwimmer and Janeane Garofalo , with a supporting cast featuring Judah Friedlander , Dick Cavett , Susan Lynch , John Krasinski , Rachel Covey , and Mia Dillon .
The movie was written and directed by Matt Mulhern and released by IFC Films in November 2005 .
The film 's plot centers on the title character  (  Schwimmer  )  , an alcoholic whose life is spiraling downward rapidly after his divorce from Linda  (  Garofalo  )  .
The movie , writer/director Matt Mulhern 's second film , was well received by critics , named by Roger Ebert as `` one of the best movies of 2005 . ''
He also said that David Schwimmer gave a `` career-transforming performance . ''
IFC did not release the film in New York City or Los Angeles , focusing instead on Philadelphia , Tucson and Kansas City .
HBO released the DVD in April 2006 and Showtime and The Movie Channel began the cable run in December 2006 .

After the series finale of Friends in 2004 , Schwimmer was cast as the title character in the 2005 drama Duane Hopwood .
Her screen credits include The Money Pit , A Shock to the System , Gods and Generals , and Duane Hopwood .

Rachel Covey  (  born June 15 , 1998  )  is an American child actress known for her roles in the 2005 film Duane Hopwood alongside David Schwimmer and the 2007 Disney movie Enchanted alongside Patrick Dempsey and Amy Adams .
